    "problemStatement": "**This is the hard version of the problem. Here, P2iP_{2i}P2i\u200b may or may not be zero.**\n\nYou are given a permutation\u2020^\\dagger\u2020 PPP of the integers 111 to 2N2N2N, with some of its elements missing (represented by 000's).\n\nFind the number of ways of filling in the zeros to obtain a valid permutation, such that the quantity\n\n\u2223P1\u2212P2\u2223+\u2223P3\u2212P4\u2223+\u2026+\u2223P2N\u22121\u2212P2N\u2223|P_1 - P_2| + |P_3 - P_4| + \\ldots + |P_{2N-1} - P_{2N}|\u2223P1\u200b\u2212P2\u200b\u2223+\u2223P3\u200b\u2212P4\u200b\u2223+\u2026+\u2223P2N\u22121\u200b\u2212P2N\u200b\u2223is maximized.\n\nThe answer can be large, so find it modulo 998244353998 244 353998244353.\n\n\u2020^\\dagger\u2020 A permutation of the integers 111 to NNN is an array of length NNN that contains every integer from 111 to NNN exactly once.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of two lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN \u2014 meaning that PPP has length 2N2N2N.\nThe second line contains 2N2N2N space-separated integers P1,P2,\u2026,P2NP_1, P_2, \\ldots, P_{2N}P1\u200b,P2\u200b,\u2026,P2N\u200b.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the number of ways of filling in the zeros to maximize the sum, modulo 998244353998 244 353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "1\u2264N\u22642\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 2\\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22642\u22c5105",
      "0\u2264Pi\u22642N0 \\leq P_i \\leq 2N0\u2264Pi\u200b\u22642N",
      "All the non-zero elements of PPP are distinct.",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 2\u22c51052\\cdot 10^52\u22c5105."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
